# Generate Comparison

## Goal
Build a structured comparison between entities or concepts in the {{config.project.name}} wiki.

<workflow>

<step n="1" goal="Identify comparison subjects">
  <action>Determine which entities or concepts the user wants to compare</action>
  <action>Verify that wiki pages exist for each subject</action>
  <check if="a subject page does not exist">
    <action>Warn the user and ask if they want to proceed with available information</action>
  </check>
</step>

<step n="2" goal="Apply lifecycle filter to wiki sources">
  <action>Before reading pages from the wiki, exclude any page whose frontmatter has `status: superseded` or `status: archived` — those are historical record by definition, not current claims.</action>
  <action>Proceed only with pages marked `status: current` (or pages with no `status` field set, which lint treats as `current` by default).</action>
  <check if="this deliverable specifically requires historical context (e.g., a before/after comparison or a retrospective)">
    <action>Include superseded pages explicitly, and annotate every claim drawn from them — in tables, italicize the row and add "(historical)"; in prose, footnote-link to the superseding page using {{config.wiki.cross_ref_style}}.</action>
  </check>
  <check if="any included page has `last_verified` older than {{config.maturity.decay_threshold_days}} days">
    <action>Annotate that claim with a "verification age" marker in the output (e.g., "last verified {N} days ago") so the reader can judge freshness without leaving the document.</action>
  </check>
</step>

<step n="3" goal="Determine comparison dimensions">
  <action>Based on the subjects and domain, identify the most meaningful comparison attributes</action>
{{#if (eq config.workflows.ingestion_style "autonomous")}}
  <action>Proceed with the identified dimensions — log the choice with `[AUTO] comparison-dimensions | selected: {dimensions list}`</action>
{{else}}
  <action>Present the proposed dimensions to the user for confirmation</action>
{{/if}}
  <action>Read all relevant wiki pages to gather data for each dimension</action>
</step>

<step n="4" goal="Build comparison table">
  <action>Create a markdown table with subjects as columns and attributes as rows</action>
  <action>Fill in data from wiki pages, citing sources for each cell</action>
  <action>Mark cells where data is missing or uncertain</action>
</step>

<step n="5" goal="Write analysis">
  <action>Below the table, write a narrative analysis of key differences and similarities</action>
  <action>Highlight surprising findings or important distinctions</action>
  <action>Note where data gaps limit the comparison</action>
</step>

<step n="6" goal="Save and index">
  <action>Save to `wiki/comparisons/{subject-a}-vs-{subject-b}.md` using the comparison-table template</action>
{{#if config.wiki.frontmatter}}
  <action>Include frontmatter: type: comparison, subjects list, created date, source_count</action>
{{/if}}
  <action>Add the comparison to `wiki/index.md` under the Comparisons category</action>
  <action>Log the comparison in `wiki/log.md`</action>
</step>

</workflow>
